cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, specifically on crowd counting using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for crowd counting using top-down feedback, which involves using feedback from a separate network to correct the initial prediction of the bottom-up network. This approach involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed architecture, which involves training the network using large datasets, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. The paper also involves the use of multimedia data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
